==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mare clausum
<hw>Ma"re clau"sum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Internat. Law)</fld> <def>Lit., closed sea; hence, a body of water
within the separate jurisdiction of the nation; -- opposed to
<contr>open sea</contr> (<contr>mare liberum</contr>), the water open to
all nations and over which no single nation has special
control.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mareis</ent>⟦br⟧
